  <description type="morphology">Basal leaves oblanceolate to obovate, usually crenate. Involucres usually 2.6–4.2+ mm (larger in tetraploids). Disc corolla lobes 0.5–0.9(–1) mm. Cypselae usually only sparsely strigose; pappi usually not or barely exceeding ray corolla tubes and bases of disc corolla lobes. 2n = 18, 36.</description>
